2026-04-21 01:27:44 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['PSU-to-Control inter-module cable connection (both leads)'] hypothesis_explanation='The observation shows that the two leads between the power-supply module and the control module are cross‑connected: the PSU positive output is connected to the control module’s negative input and vice versa. This exactly matches the designed condition for the red “inverted cables indicator” LED to light. With the control-module polarity reversed relative to the power supply, the load module never sees a correct 12V/0V orientation at its diode input, so no current can reach the lamp, even when the switch is closed. No internal component appears faulty; the fault is a configuration error in the PSU-to-control cabling polarity. Correcting these two connections (PSU+→Control+, PSU−→Control−) should extinguish the red LED and allow the lamp to operate normally when the switch is closed.'
